This fails: (note in circle.js, 'exports' is qualified with 'module.' 

 -- foo.js --
    'use strict';

```
 const circle = require('./circle');
 console.log( `The area of a circle of radius 4 is ${circle.area(4)}`);

 circle.   <= you DON't get 'circumference'
