I'd like to add a feature to automatically fill "files to include" with the currently focused directory when opening the search. It is quite handy and other IDEs offer this feature, too.
So if you focus the folder "foo" in tree of the "Explorer" view and you press ⌘⇧F, than "files to include" should be filled with "foo", so the user can search directly in "foo".

The search value is automatically filled, too, if you have text selected in the editor. This happens in `getSelectionFromEditor` and is possible because the "Search" view has access to the editor (`this.editorService.getActiveEditor().getControl()`).

I tried to find a way to get the focused element in the tree "Explorer" view. 

This is possible in `OpenSearchViewletAction`:

```
class OpenSearchViewletAction extends ToggleViewletAction {
    public static ID = VIEWLET_ID;
    public static LABEL = nls.localize('showSearchViewlet', "Show Search");

    constructor(id: string, label: string, @IViewletService viewletService: IViewletService, @IWorkbenchEditorService editorService: IWorkbenchEditorService) {
        if (viewletService.getActiveViewlet() instanceof ExplorerViewlet) {
            const viewer = (<ExplorerViewlet>viewletService.getActiveViewlet()).getExplorerView().getViewer();
            console.log(viewer.getFocus());
        }
        super(id, label, VIEWLET_ID, viewletService, editorService);
    }
}
```

This will call `this.viewletService.openViewlet(this.viewletId, true);` (in `ToggleViewletAction#run`) later, so we switch to the "Search" view. It seems there is no way to pass the focused element from the tree "Explorer" view to the "Search" view here, so I can fill "files to include".

Any hint how I can do that...?

- VSCode Version: 0.10.11
- OS Version: OS X El Capitan v 10.11.4

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a new file with the extension `.es6` and the following code

   ``` javascript
   class Testing {
      constructor() {
          this.myValue = "Hello World";
      }

      test() {
          return this.myValue;
      }
   }
   ```
2. The Language Mode is automatically set to "JavaScript", but on `this.myValue` you get `Property 'myValue' does not exist on type 'Testing'` errors.
3. Close the file and rename it to use a `.js` extension
4. Open the file and notice that the errors are gone
